nhc_headline: ...IMELDA CONTINUES NORTHWARD AND A LITTLE STRONGER... ...TROPICAL STORM CONDITIONS CONTINUE OVER THE NORTHWEST BAHAMAS THIS MORNING...
summary: ...IMELDA CONTINUES NORTHWARD AND A LITTLE STRONGER... ...TROPICAL STORM CONDITIONS CONTINUE OVER THE NORTHWEST BAHAMAS THIS MORNING... As of 8:00 AM EDT Mon Sep 29 the center of Imelda was located near 26.3, -77.0 with movement N at 9 mph. The minimum central pressure was 993 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 50 mph.
